5. Falsifier map

Each gate needs a falsifier.

FalsifierMap_RH_v8_4 = {
  PrincipalPartProtection:
    falsified if local / regular sector can lawfully cancel zero principal parts.
  ProtectedShortedWeilPositivity:
    falsified if shorted Weil form exists but does not equal/support K_PP
    in the correct positivity direction.
  FiniteGramTheorem:
    falsified if a finite off-circle reciprocal-conjugate block system
    has PSD K_PP.
  tauPP_scale:
    falsified if every topology controlling the tail makes some
    off-circle defect infinite-cost.
  LiPacketIsolation:
    falsified if no moment-cancelled packet can beat TargetGain vs TailLeak.
  DiffuseShorting:
    falsified if diffuse shield survives protected shorting as positive shield.
  CoherentPromotion:
    falsified if a coherent shield hides target but cannot be retargeted.
  NoNeutralCycle:
    falsified if coherent shield recursion cycles with bounded energy.
  KHRecovery:
    falsified if PSD K_PP exists but cannot be represented by a unitary orbit.
}

This is important because it prevents the architecture from becoming unfalsifiable.

